narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: gained more knowledge on some of the seminal papers in stem cell biology

This was a very interesting survey course where I learned about the different areas of research in the stem cell field. Since I'm interested in stem cell research, I will definitely use the knowledge that I've gained.
General overview of stem cell research

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: strengths - using experts in the field to lecture on the topic; covering a wide range of topics weaknesses - I think it should be required that the student presenters attempt to engage the rest of the class in the discussion about the papers. Otherwise, no one reads the papers and hardly anyone pays attention during the paper presentations.
Overall enjoyable course. Very low stress but informative.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, with reservations. I think it is a good introduction to the field of stem cells, however it could be more engaging overall. Some professors were successful in engaging the class, but most of the time everyone was disengaged.
I recommend this course to anyone who is interested in stem cell research.
